---

<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0" />
    <title>State of Design Systems 2026 | Buoy</title>
    <meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
    <style>
      @import url('https://fonts.googleapis.com/css2?family=Inter:wght@400;500;600;700&display=swap');

      * { margin: 0; padding: 0; box-sizing: border-box; }

      body {
        font-family: 'Inter', sans-serif;
        font-size: 10px;
        line-height: 1.5;
        color: #1a1a1a;
        background: white;
        padding: 0.4in;
        max-width: 8.5in;
        margin: 0 auto;
      }

      @media print {
        body { padding: 0.3in; }
        .no-print { display: none !important; }
      }

      .header {
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        align-items: flex-start;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
        padding-bottom: 12px;
        border-bottom: 2px solid #0ea5e9;
      }

      .logo { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; color: #F97316; }
      h1 { font-size: 18px; font-weight: 700; text-align: right; }
      .subtitle { font-size: 10px; color: #666; text-align: right; }

      .summary-box {
        background: #f0f9ff;
        border: 1px solid #0ea5e9;
        border-radius: 8px;
        padding: 12px;
        margin-bottom: 16px;
      }

      .summary-box h2 {
        font-size: 11px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
      }

      .stats-row {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(5, 1fr);
        gap: 8px;
      }

      .stat {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 8px;
        background: white;
        border-radius: 6px;
      }

      .stat-value {
        font-size: 18px;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #0ea5e9;
      }

      .stat-label {
        font-size: 8px;
        color: #666;
        margin-top: 2px;
      }

      h2 {
        font-size: 12px;
        font-weight: 700;
        margin-top: 14px;
        margin-bottom: 8px;
        padding: 4px 8px;
        background: #f0f9ff;
        border-left: 3px solid #0ea5e9;
      }

      .finding {
        margin-bottom: 12px;
        break-inside: avoid;
      }

      .finding-header {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 8px;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }

      .finding-num {
        background: #0ea5e9;
        color: white;
        font-size: 10px;
        font-weight: 700;
        width: 20px;
        height: 20px;
        border-radius: 50%;
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: center;
      }

      .finding-title { font-size: 11px; font-weight: 600; }

      .finding-stat {
        font-size: 10px;
        color: #0ea5e9;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 2px;
      }

      .finding-desc {
        font-size: 9px;
        color: #666;
      }

      .data-table {
        width: 100%;
        border-collapse: collapse;
        font-size: 9px;
        margin: 8px 0;
      }

      .data-table th {
        background: #f8f9fa;
        padding: 6px 8px;
        text-align: left;
        font-weight: 600;
        border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
      }

      .data-table td {
        padding: 6px 8px;
        border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
      }

      .benchmark-grid {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: repeat(4, 1fr);
        gap: 6px;
        margin: 10px 0;
      }

      .benchmark {
        text-align: center;
        padding: 8px;
        border-radius: 6px;
      }

      .benchmark.poor { background: #fef2f2; border: 1px solid #fecaca; }
      .benchmark.avg { background: #fffbeb; border: 1px solid #fde68a; }
      .benchmark.good { background: #f0fdf4; border: 1px solid #bbf7d0; }
      .benchmark.excellent { background: #f0f9ff; border: 1px solid #7dd3fc; }

      .benchmark-label {
        font-size: 10px;
        font-weight: 600;
      }

      .benchmark.poor .benchmark-label { color: #dc2626; }
      .benchmark.avg .benchmark-label { color: #d97706; }
      .benchmark.good .benchmark-label { color: #16a34a; }
      .benchmark.excellent .benchmark-label { color: #0284c7; }

      .benchmark-value {
        font-size: 8px;
        color: #666;
        margin-top: 2px;
      }

      .grid-2 {
        display: grid;
        grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr;
        gap: 12px;
      }

      .rec-box {
        background: #f8f9fa;
        border: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
        border-radius: 6px;
        padding: 10px;
      }

      .rec-num {
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 700;
        color: #0ea5e9;
        margin-bottom: 4px;
      }

      .rec-title {
        font-size: 10px;
        font-weight: 600;
        margin-bottom: 2px;
      }

      .rec-desc {
        font-size: 8px;
        color: #666;
      }

      .cta {
        margin-top: 14px;
        padding: 12px;
        background: #f8f9fa;
        border: 1px solid #F97316;
        border-radius: 8px;
        text-align: center;
      }

      .cta h3 { font-size: 11px; margin-bottom: 4px; }
      .cta p { font-size: 9px; color: #666; margin-bottom: 6px; }
      .cta-link {
        display: inline-block;
        padding: 6px 16px;
        background: #F97316;
        color: white;
        font-size: 9px;
        font-weight: 600;
        text-decoration: none;
        border-radius: 6px;
      }

      .footer {
        margin-top: 12px;
        padding-top: 8px;
        border-top: 1px solid #e5e5e5;
        display: flex;
        justify-content: space-between;
        font-size: 8px;
        color: #999;
      }

      .print-button {
        position: fixed;
        top: 20px;
        right: 20px;
        padding: 12px 24px;
        background: #F97316;
        color: white;
        border: none;
        border-radius: 8px;
        font-size: 14px;
        font-weight: 600;
        cursor: pointer;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <button class="print-button no-print" onclick="window.print()">Save as PDF</button>

    <header class="header">
      <div class="logo">Buoy</div>
      <div>
        <h1>The State of Design Systems 2026</h1>
        <p class="subtitle">Based on analysis of 500+ repositories</p>
      </div>
    </header>

    <div class="summary-box">
      <h2>Executive Summary</h2>
      <div class="stats-row">
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">73%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">have significant drift</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">847</div>
          <div class="stat-label">avg hardcoded colors</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">2.4x</div>
          <div class="stat-label">more drift after 3 years</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">23%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">token adoption rate</div>
        </div>
        <div class="stat">
          <div class="stat-value">68%</div>
          <div class="stat-label">less drift with automation</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <h2>Key Findings</h2>

    <div class="finding">
      <div class="finding-header">
        <span class="finding-num">1</span>
        <span class="finding-title">Design Drift Is Universal</span>
      </div>
      <div class="finding-stat">Only 8% of codebases have minimal drift</div>
      <div class="finding-desc">Even teams with dedicated design systems, Storybook documentation, and Figma libraries show significant drift when we scan the actual code.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="finding">
      <div class="finding-header">
        <span class="finding-num">2</span>
        <span class="finding-title">The 847 Problem</span>
      </div>
      <div class="finding-stat">Average: 847 hardcoded colors | Top 10%: Nearly 3,000</div>
      <div class="finding-desc">In repos with hardcoded colors, we found an average of 47 unique variations of the primary brand color.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="finding">
      <div class="finding-header">
        <span class="finding-num">3</span>
        <span class="finding-title">Drift Compounds Over Time</span>
      </div>
      <table class="data-table">
        <tr><th>Repo Age</th><th>0-1 yr</th><th>1-2 yr</th><th>2-3 yr</th><th>3-4 yr</th><th>4+ yr</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Avg Drift Score</td><td>312</td><td>489</td><td>634</td><td>758</td><td>847</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <div class="finding">
      <div class="finding-header">
        <span class="finding-num">4</span>
        <span class="finding-title">Token Adoption Is Low</span>
      </div>
      <div class="finding-stat">67% hardcoded | 23% CSS variables | 8% theme objects</div>
      <div class="finding-desc">Tailwind teams show highest adoption (41%) when using custom theme colors—but arbitrary values bypass everything.</div>
    </div>

    <div class="finding">
      <div class="finding-header">
        <span class="finding-num">5</span>
        <span class="finding-title">Enforcement Changes Everything</span>
      </div>
      <table class="data-table">
        <tr><th>Enforcement</th><th>None</th><th>Code Review</th><th>Linting</th><th>Blocking CI</th><th>Auto PR Scan</th></tr>
        <tr><td>Avg Drift</td><td>891</td><td>672</td><td>423</td><td>287</td><td>201</td></tr>
      </table>
    </div>

    <h2>Benchmarks: How Do You Compare?</h2>

    <table class="data-table">
      <tr><th>Metric</th><th>Poor</th><th>Average</th><th>Good</th><th>Excellent</th></tr>
      <tr><td>Hardcoded colors</td><td>>500</td><td>200-500</td><td>50-200</td><td><50</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Token usage</td><td><15%</td><td>15-30%</td><td>30-50%</td><td>>50%</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Arbitrary values</td><td>>100</td><td>50-100</td><td>10-50</td><td><10</td></tr>
      <tr><td>Color variations</td><td>>30</td><td>15-30</td><td>5-15</td><td><5</td></tr>
    </table>

    <h2>Recommendations</h2>

    <div class="grid-2">
      <div class="rec-box">
        <div class="rec-num">1</div>
        <div class="rec-title">Automate Enforcement</div>
        <div class="rec-desc">Don't rely on code review. Use automated scanning in CI/CD. Impact: 68% less drift.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rec-box">
        <div class="rec-num">2</div>
        <div class="rec-title">Use Semantic Tokens</div>
        <div class="rec-desc">Flat palettes encourage hardcoding. Semantic tokens encourage adoption. Impact: 34% higher usage.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rec-box">
        <div class="rec-num">3</div>
        <div class="rec-title">Address Framework Defaults</div>
        <div class="rec-desc">Customize the entire palette. Remove unused defaults. Impact: 43% fewer mixed colors.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="rec-box">
        <div class="rec-num">4</div>
        <div class="rec-title">Measure Continuously</div>
        <div class="rec-desc">What gets measured gets managed. Track drift over time. Prevents compounding.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="cta">
      <h3>Get Your Drift Score</h3>
      <p>Buoy scans your repository and shows exactly how you compare to industry benchmarks.</p>
      <a href="https://buoy.design" class="cta-link">Scan Free at buoy.design →</a>
    </div>

    <footer class="footer">
      <span>© 2026 Buoy. The design system drift detector.</span>
      <span>buoy.design</span>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
